{"id":1723102,"retrievedAt":"2026-06-30T13:30:50.008Z","response":{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":null,"belongs_to_collection":null,"budget":0,"genres":[{"id":99,"name":"Documentary"}],"homepage":"","id":1723102,"imdb_id":null,"origin_country":["NL"],"original_language":"nl","original_title":"De film die nooit afkwam","overview":"In the late 1970s, filmmaker Frans Bromet worked on a film about Holocaust survivor and painter Sieg Maandag. The film was intended to answer the question of how one can continue living after a concentration camp.  Sieg Maandag was the little boy in the famous photo in the American magazine LIFE, walking towards his freedom shortly after the liberation of the Bergen-Belsen concentration camp. The film 'Life’s Picture' was never completed at the time due to a conflict between Bromet and the producer, who envisioned a heroic film about the Second World War, whereas Bromet wanted to keep it small and personal.  Behind the search for answers to the question of why the film failed, a loving monument emerges to a survivor who, despite the misery he endured, managed to create a life in which optimism and inspiration predominated.","popularity":0.0786,"poster_path":"/ea3W7eVqWU99kUV0xnWMSPSwmMs.jpg","production_companies":[{"id":84608,"logo_path":null,"name":"&Bromet","origin_country":"NL"},{"id":107563,"logo_path":"/x42HkwWO4sOYSekXbl3LKxRz2Wo.png","name":"EO","origin_country":"NL"}],"production_countries":[{"iso_3166_1":"NL","name":"Netherlands"}],"release_date":"2017-05-04","revenue":0,"runtime":57,"softcore":false,"spoken_languages":[{"english_name":"Dutch","iso_639_1":"nl","name":"Nederlands"}],"status":"Released","tagline":"","title":"De film die nooit afkwam","video":false,"vote_average":0,"vote_count":0,"alternative_titles":{"titles":[]},"credits":{"cast":[{"adult":false,"gender":2,"id":26573,"known_for_department":"Camera","name":"Frans Bromet","original_name":"Frans Bromet","popularity":0.2077,"profile_path":"/xkAmDZ4kDZKSBGbU6597MnCtYA3.j